69th Legislature 2025 LC 1323
1
2 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Short title. [Sections 1 and 2] may be cited as the "Montana Hunters
3 First Act".
4
5 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Nonresident hunting impact study. (1) The department of fish, wildlife,
6 and parks shall conduct a study of nonresident impacts on deer and elk hunting in the state and in each of the
7 fish and wildlife commission's administrative regions.
8 (2) The study must utilize a range of data, including but not limited to hunter days, harvest
9 reporting, use of lands that are part of hunting access programs, hunting pressure on public lands, elk and deer
10 population trends, and licensing.
11 (3) Upon completion of the study, the department shall publish a report that is accessible to the
12 public. The report must include:
13 (a) a comprehensive assessment of the data as it relates to nonresident impacts on deer and elk
14 hunting in the state and in each of the commission's administrative regions;
15 (b) specific information about the methods used for collecting or acquiring data used in the report;
16 and
17 (c) the identification of specific issues for consideration by the legislature, department, and
18 commission concerning nonresident impacts on deer and elk hunting.
19 (4) The study and report must be completed by December 1, 2026.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Termination. [Sections 1 and 2] terminate December 31, 2026.
